     Internet
        |
     Server
        |
     Response
        |
     Browser

 
 3> Network vs Internet

  # Network
 
 A network is a connection betweeen two or more devices.
 
  Example: Home wi-fi Network.


  # Internet

  The Internet is a network of network.

  it connects million of networks around the world.


  4> IP Address

  = An IP (Internet Protocol) Address is a unique address assigned to a
    dedvice on a network.

   It helps data reach the correct destination.

  
  # Example
  
 Laptop > 192.168.1.10
 Phone  > 192.168.1.20



 5> Public IP vs Private IP

 # Public IP

  Accessible over the Internet.
 
  Used to communicate with devices from anywhere in the world.


 # Private IP

 Used only inside a local network.
 
 Not directly accessible from the internet.

 
 6> Packets

 = A packets is small peice of data sent over a network.

  > Large files are divided into many packets before transmission.

  > At the destination, all packets are reassembled into the original file.

 # A packet contains

 i> source IP Address
 ii> Destination IP Address
 iii> A portion of the data


